        <h1 id="person">What is a Person Resource</h1>
        <a href="#body" class="top" title="Back up to the top of the page" >Top</a>
      </div>
      <div class="body">
        <p>
           One of the simpliest resources to describe is a <a taget="_blank" href="http://spase-group.org/data/search.jsp?term=Person&style=entry">Person</a>. 
           A <a target="_blank" href="http://spase-group.org/data/search.jsp?term=Person&style=entry">Person</a> resource can be
           used to describe any individual or group of individuals. This includes an organization
           such as a research group, institute or university.
           The only required elements for a <a taget="_blank" href="http://spase-group.org/data/search.jsp?term=Person&style=entry">Person</a> 
           resource are a resource ID and an organization name.
           Often, other elements are included in order to provide a more complete description.
         </p>
     </div> <!-- End of Body -->
   </div> <!-- End of Section -->

    <div class="section">
      <div class="head">
        <h1 id="example">Example</h1>
        <a href="#body" class="top" title="Back up to the top of the page" >Top</a>
      </div>
      <div class="body">
        <p>
        	The most basic Person resource description can describe an organization:
        	<pre class="code">
&lt;Spase>
   &lt;Person>
      &lt;ResourceID>spase://smwg/Person/SPASE.School&lt;/ResourceID>
      &lt;OrganizationName>SPASE School&lt;/OrganizationName>
   &lt;/Person>
&lt;/Spase>
        	</pre>
         </p>
        <p>
        	A Person resource description for an actual person:
        	<pre class="code">
&lt;Person&gt;
   &lt;ResourceID&gt;spase://SMWG/Person/Todd.A.King&lt;/ResourceID&gt;
   &lt;ReleaseDate&gt;2010-08-05T17:35:47Z&lt;/ReleaseDate&gt;
   &lt;PersonName&gt;Todd A. King&lt;/PersonName&gt;
   &lt;OrganizationName&gt;
      Institute of Geophysics and Planetary Physics, University of California, Los Angeles
   &lt;/OrganizationName&gt;
   &lt;Address&gt;
      Institute of Geophysics and Planetary Physics, University of California Los Angeles, Box 951567, Los Angeles, CA 90095-1567
   &lt;/Address&gt;
   &lt;Email&gt;tking@igpp.ucla.edu&lt;/Email&gt;
   &lt;PhoneNumber&gt;+1 310 206 7201&lt;/PhoneNumber&gt;
&lt;/Person&gt;
</pre>
         </p>
